<div class="panel panel-default">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <h3 class="panel-title">Target Server</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-body">
    <p>Create <code><%= sample_path %></code> to permit this online analysis. The path must return a 2xx status code to proceed.</p>
    <p>The tests will create numerous anonymous identities. If you wish to tag identities for cleanup, the test client will identify it's agent as <code>SQRL/1 SQRL::Check/<var>version</var></code> for SQRL requests and <code>SQRL::Check/<var>version</var></code> for plain HTTP requests. Feedback is welcome on possible SQRL options etc. that could be used to tag test accounts.</p>

    <form method="post" action="/results" class="form-horizontal">
      <div class="form-group">
        <label for="target_url" class="control-label col-sm-2">Target Url</label>
        <div class="col-sm-10">
          <input type="text" size="40" id="target_url" name="target_url" placeholder="https://" class="form-control" aria-describedby="target_url_html"/>
          <p class="help-block" id="target_url_html">HTML URL that contains nonced SQRL URL</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="form-group">
        <div class="col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-10">
          <div class="checkbox">
            <label for="signed_cert" class="control-label">
              <input type="checkbox" id="signed_cert" name="signed_cert" aria-describedby="self_signed"/>
              Check TLS certificate signing chain
            </label>
            <p class="help-block" id="self_signed">Leave off for self-signed certs</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="form-group">
        <div class="col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-10">
          <input type="submit" value="Run" class="btn btn-default">
        </div>
      </div>
    </form>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="panel panel-default">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <h3 class="panel-title">SQRL::Test demo server</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-body">
    <form method="post" action="/results" class="form-horizontal">
      <div class="form-group">
        <label for="target_url_test" class="control-label col-sm-2">Demo URL</label>
        <div class="col-sm-4">
          <input type="text" size="40" id="target_url_test" name="target_url" value="https://sqrl-test.herokuapp.com/" readonly="readonly" class="form-control"/>
        </div>
        <input type="hidden" id="signed_cert" name="signed_cert" value="true"/>
        <div class="col-sm-6">
          <input type="submit" value="Run Demo" class="btn btn-default">
        </div>
      </div>
    </form>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="panel panel-default">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <h3 class="panel-title">This server</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-body">
    <form method="post" action="/results" class="form-horizontal">
      <div class="form-group">
        <label for="target_url_self" class="control-label col-sm-2">Demo URL</label>
        <div class="col-sm-4">
          <input type="text" size="40" id="target_url_self" name="target_url" value="<%= our_url %>" readonly="readonly" class="form-control"/>
          <p class="help-block">Uses only browser session auth, persistence tests expected to fail.</p>
        </div>
        <input type="hidden" id="signed_cert" name="signed_cert" value="true"/>
        <div class="col-sm-6">
          <input type="submit" value="Run Demo" class="btn btn-default">
        </div>
      </div>
    </form>
  </div>
</div>

